                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 337.11/390</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-03-31T17:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 31, 1917, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>It has been reported great damage has been done Cuban Railroad Company line
                    between Santiago and San Luis and San Luis and Marti. The Department is
                    disturbed, as we understand that the censorship is so strict that no information
                    is getting through.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
